Changes to a production vehicle from one model year to the next are often marginal, if not nonexistent. But with a performance model like the Porsche 911 GT3, you can't get away with not pushing further alongside your competition. And as 2016 rolled over to 2017, the GT3 saw one of its biggest changes in years. The famous flat-six that powers the driver's 911 was bumped up to a nice, round, 4.0-liter displacement. That resulted in an even 500-horsepower output, matching the outgoing GT3 RS and trending the more affordable GT3 model even further up the ladder. New shocks, rubber, and rear-wheel steering are among the smaller changes that add up to the 991.2 GT3's all-around prowess on road and track.
